properties.name: Anaheim, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37The location of Disneyland. (along with Paris, Orlando and some place in Japan). I stayed most of my nights here (only 1 day in Disneyland, though. Well I couldn\'t miss out, could I?)

properties.name: Beverley Hills, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37The place where only celebritys live. The most interesting thing to do here is to slowly drive down the streets and stare at the famous-people\'s houses, and even that is pretty pointless, seeing as they all have huge security gates that block any good view of their mansions. The roads are still very pretty here though, with trees lined along them.

properties.name: Death Valley, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37Hottest place on Earth. Damn right! Walking around here felt like walking in an oven. There were still some spectacular sights though, such as the salty, dried up land (I know it dosn\'t sound too exciting, but it was pretty. I can\'t remember its name though). I remember that I couldn\'t stand there and look at it for too long, becuase the heat would become too much.

properties.name: Hollywood, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37Go there just to walk down Sunset Blvd, looking at the famous stars paved into the \'sidewalk\'. Those Americans.

properties.name: LAX (airport), 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37The airport from which we arrived and departed from. Where our adventure began and ended.

properties.name: Lake Tahoe, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37Not a particulary beautiful lake as far as I can remember, but still a nice place to eat a Californian melon.

properties.name: Las Vegas, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37I was excited about visiting \'America\'s playground\', but was distinctly disappointed when I got there. Cockroaches swarming the pavements, numerous prostitute cards scattered around. Although walking down the Strip was memorable. =)

properties.name: Monument Valley, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37Spent the whole day there. Maonument Valley is around here, right? Such an amazing and awe-inspiring landscape and landmark, anyway. Got posters of it plastered all over my kitchen wall- I can come back to it every time I enter my kitchen!

properties.name: Newport Beach
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37  I wanted to go here, just becuase my favourite TV show is set here: The OC, of course! I didn\'t get to go in the end though =(

properties.name: Salt Lake City, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37Just drove through it in the late evening. I think there were nice stars in the sky. Didn\'t stop in the city, so didn\'t get to know it at all.

properties.name: San Francisco, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37I didn\'t realise how many hills there were in SF! Also how cramped it is. It was still brilliant just walking down the streets, feeling the SF atmosphere. Also driving along the world-famous Gold Gate Bridge was good, although the thick fog was disappinting. Something quite depressing as well as alarming were the many homeless people scavenging the streets- surprising from such a rich and famous city as SF.

properties.name: Santa Barbara, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37SB was a town with pretty and interesting architecture- the houses were Spanish-like, with terecotta(?) rooves. Made the town Meditarrean-esque. A huge and amazing pastel sketch on the ground there.

properties.name: Santa Monica, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37Is this the place where Michael Jackson lives? Or is that Carmel? I can\'t really remember what SM was like.

properties.name: Sequoia National Park, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37 The tallest trees in the world. Tallest tree in the world: the General Sherman. Enough said.

properties.name: Yosemite National Park, 2003 America trip
properties.description: Posted by Maxine37 Not as memoerable as the other National Parks I went to, such as the Sequoia National Park. There were some beautiful stone landscapes, though.
